label.value: cellular response to aldehyde

value.value: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an aldehyde stimulus.

label.value: spindle pole body separation

value.value: The release of duplicated spindle pole bodies (SPBs) and their migration away from each other within the nuclear membrane. Duplicated SPBs are connected by a bridge structure that is severed in order to release the SPBs from one another. Following liberation, SPBs diffuse through the nuclear membrane until they are across from each other. SPB separation must take place in order for a bipolar spindle to assemble.

definition.value: Note that this term is in the subset of terms that should not be used for direct gene product annotation. Instead, select a child term or, if no appropriate child term exists, please request a new term. Direct annotations to this term may be amended during annotation QC.

label.value: mRNA alternative polyadenylation

value.value: The process of generating multiple mRNA molecules with variable 3'-end length formation from a given pre-mRNA by differential use of cleavage and polyadenylation signals (pA signals).

label.value: mRNA cleavage and polyadenylation specificity factor complex assembly

value.value: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form the mRNA cleavage and polyadenylation specificity factor complex.

label.value: Cdr2 medial cortical node complex

value.value: A megadalton-sized complex at the medial cortex organized as an oligomeric core of SAD family protein kinases involved in cell size-dependent localization and phosphorylation of Wee1 during interphase.

label.value: RNA decapping

value.value: Cleavage of the 5'-cap of an RNA.

label.value: methylguanosine-cap decapping

value.value: Cleavage of the 5'-methylguanosine-cap of an mRNA. The methylguanosine-cap is present at the 5'-end of eukaryotic mRNAs. Decapping inactivates translation initiation and promotes 5'-to-3' decay of mRNA.

label.value: regulation of mitotic spindle formation (spindle phase one)

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the cell cycle process in which the distance is lengthened between poles of the mitotic spindle during mitotic prophase (spindle phase one).

label.value: negative regulation of mitotic spindle formation (spindle phase one)

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the cell cycle process in which the distance is lengthened between poles of the mitotic spindle during mitotic prophase (spindle phase one).

label.value: positive regulation of mitotic spindle formation (spindle phase one)

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the cell cycle process in which the distance is lengthened between poles of the mitotic spindle during mitotic prophase (spindle phase one).

label.value: regulation of mitotic spindle elongation (spindle phase three)

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the cell cycle process in which the distance is lengthened between poles of the mitotic spindle during mitotic anaphase B (spindle phase three).

label.value: negative regulation of mitotic spindle elongation (spindle phase three)

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the cell cycle process in which the distance is lengthened between poles of the mitotic spindle during mitotic anaphase B (spindle phase three).

label.value: positive regulation of mitotic spindle elongation (spindle phase three)

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the cell cycle process in which the distance is lengthened between poles of the mitotic spindle during mitotic anaphase B (spindle phase three).

label.value: cellular anatomical entity

value.value: A part of a cellular organism that is either an immaterial entity or a material entity with granularity above the level of a protein complex but below that of an anatomical system. Or, a substance produced by a cellular organism with granularity above the level of a protein complex.

label.value: DNA synthesis involved in mitochondrial DNA replication

value.value: Any DNA biosynthetic process that is involved in mitochondrial DNA replication.

label.value: plasma membrane bounded cell projection

value.value: A prolongation or process extending from a cell and that is bounded by plasma membrane, e.g. a cilium, lamellipodium, or axon.

label.value: proton export across plasma membrane

value.value: The directed movement of hydrogen ions (protons) from inside a cell, across the plasma membrane and into the extracellular region.

label.value: plasma membrane bounded cell projection assembly

value.value: Formation of a prolongation or process extending and that is bounded by plasma membrane, e.g. a cilium, lamellipodium, or axon.

label.value: regulation of plasma membrane bounded cell projection assembly

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of plasma membrane bounded cell projection assembly.

label.value: negative regulation of plasma membrane bounded cell projection assembly

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of plasma membrane bounded cell projection assembly.

label.value: positive regulation of plasma membrane bounded cell projection assembly

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of plasma membrane bounded cell projection assembly.

label.value: regulation of plasma membrane bounded cell projection organization

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a process involved in the formation, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of plasma membrane bounded cell projections.

label.value: plasma membrane bounded cell projection organization

value.value: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a plasma membrane bounded prolongation or process extending from a cell, e.g. a cilium or axon.

label.value: regulation of protein localization to medial cortical node

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to a medial cortical node.

label.value: positive regulation of protein localization to medial cortical node

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to a medial cortical node.

label.value: DNA-3'-diphospho-5'-guanosine diphosphatase

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: (DNA)-3'-diphospho-5'-guanosine + H2O = (DNA)-3'-phosphate + GMP.

label.value: mitotic telomere clustering and tethering at nuclear periphery

value.value: The process in which the telomeres are gathered together to a small number of foci per chromosome (usually one per chromosome or fewer), and moved to and tethered at the nuclear periphery, as part of a mitotic cell cycle.

label.value: interphase mitotic telomere clustering

value.value: The process whereby the mitotic telomeres are gathered together during, or prior to, attachment to the nuclear envelope.

definition.value: It is likely that both intra chromosome telomere clustering and inter-chromosome occur because a single focus is sometimes observed, although this has yet to be proven.

label.value: cytoplasm to vacuole transport by the NVT pathway

value.value: A pathway targeting soluble cytosolic proteins to the vacuole lumen. It uses a selective autophagy receptor protein Nbr1, which is an ortholog of mammalian NBR1, and is remotely related to S. cerevisiae Cvt pathway receptor protein Atg19. Similar to the Cvt pathway, the cargos transported by this pathway are hydrolases, which presumably contribute to the hydrolytic activities in the vacuole lumen. Different from the Cvt pathway, this pathway does not require the macroautophagy machinery, but instead relies on the ESCRT machinery for cargo sequestration. This pathway is observed in the fission yeast S. pombe.

label.value: Sm-like protein family complex

value.value: A protein complex containing members of the Like-Sm family of proteins, which includes both the Sm proteins and the Lsm proteins, and which generally form hexameric or heptameric ring structures which bind to RNA. While some of these ring complexes may form independently of RNA, many only form in association with their target RNA. In addition to Lsm-family proteins, many of these complexes contain additional protein members. Members of this family of complexes include the snRNPs which comprise the majority of the spliceosome. Others are involved in the 5' to 3' degradation pathways of mRNAs in the cytoplasm and of unspliced transcripts in the nucleus, as well as other diverse roles.

label.value: Lsm2-8 complex

value.value: A heteroheptameric, nuclear protein complex composed of Lsm2, Lsm3, Lsm4, Lsm5, Lsm6, Lsm7, and Lsm8, or orthologs thereof, that selectively binds to snRNAs, in particular U6 or U6atac snRNAs, and also to unspliced transcripts localized within the nucleus.

label.value: response to copper ion starvation

value.value: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a starvation stimulus, deprivation of copper ion.

label.value: response to zinc ion starvation

value.value: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a starvation stimulus, deprivation of zinc ion.

label.value: negative regulation of actin cortical patch assembly

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the assembly of actin cortical patches.

label.value: regulation of mitotic actomyosin contractile ring disassembly

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of mitotic actomyosin contractile ring disassembly.

label.value: positive regulation of mitotic actomyosin contractile ring disassembly

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of mitotic actomyosin contractile ring disassembly.

label.value: MBF transcription complex assembly

value.value: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form an MBF transcription complex.

label.value: negative regulation of protein localization to chromatin

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to chromatin.

label.value: positive regulation of protein localization to chromatin

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to chromatin.

label.value: negative regulation of termination of RNA polymerase II transcription

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of termination of RNA polymerase II transcription.

label.value: regulation of heterochromatin organization

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, extent or location of heterochromatin organization.

label.value: negative regulation of heterochromatin organization

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of heterochromatin organization.

label.value: positive regulation of heterochromatin organization

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of heterochromatin organization.

label.value: regulation of chromosome attachment to the nuclear envelope

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, extent or location of chromosome attachment to the nuclear envelope.

label.value: negative regulation of chromosome attachment to the nuclear envelope

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the chromosome attachment to the nuclear envelope.

label.value: positive regulation of chromosome attachment to the nuclear envelope

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chromosome attachment to the nuclear envelope.

label.value: regulation of pigmentation

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the deposition or modulates the distribution of coloring matter in an organism.

label.value: meiotic nuclear division

value.value: One of the two nuclear divisions that occur as part of the meiotic cell cycle.

label.value: mitotic nuclear division

value.value: A mitotic cell cycle process comprising the steps by which the nucleus of a eukaryotic cell divides; the process involves condensation of chromosomal DNA into a highly compacted form. Canonically, mitosis produces two daughter nuclei whose chromosome complement is identical to that of the mother cell.

label.value: exocytic process

value.value: The cellular processes that contribute to exocytosis.
